40|$|For a given <b>binary</b> BCH <b>code</b> Cn {{of length}} n = 2 s - 1 {{generated}} by a polynomial of degree r there is no <b>binary</b> BCH <b>code</b> of length (n + 1) n {{generated by a}} generalized polynomial of degree 2 r. However, it does exist a <b>binary</b> <b>cyclic</b> <b>code</b> C (n+ 1) n of length (n + 1) n such that the <b>binary</b> BCH <b>code</b> Cn is embedded in C (n+ 1) n. Accordingly a high code rate is attained through a <b>binary</b> <b>cyclic</b> <b>code</b> C (n+ 1) n for a <b>binary</b> BCH <b>code</b> Cn. Furthermore, an algorithm proposed facilitates in a decoding of a <b>binary</b> BCH <b>code</b> Cn through the decoding of a <b>binary</b> <b>cyclic</b> <b>code</b> C (n+ 1) n, while the codes Cn and C (n+ 1) n have the same minimum hamming distance...|$|R
