40|$|In this paper, an {{explicit}} construction of <b>binary</b> self-dual <b>cyclic</b> <b>codes</b> of length going to infinity with a minimal distance {{at least half}} the square root of is presented. The same idea is also used to construct more general <b>binary</b> <b>cyclic</b> <b>codes</b> with a large minimal distance. Finally, in the special case of self-dual cyclic codes, a simplified version of a proof by Conway and Sloane is given, showing an upper bound for the distance of <b>binary</b> self-dual <b>codes...</b>|$|R
